# Page Navigation Pattern

Every page (except the home page at `src/app/page.tsx`) must include:

1. A **"Home" back link** with `ArrowLeft` icon on the left
2. The **`UserMenu`** component on the right

## Standard Header Template

```tsx
import Link from "next/link";
import { ArrowLeft } from "lucide-react";
import { UserMenu } from "@/components/user-menu";

// Inside the page component's return:
<header className="sticky top-0 z-10 bg-background/95 backdrop-blur supports-[backdrop-filter]:bg-background/60 border-b px-4 py-3">
  <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
    <div>
      <Link
        href="/"
        className="flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors mb-1"
      >
        <ArrowLeft className="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
        Home
      </Link>
      <h1 className="text-xl font-bold">Page Title</h1>
    </div>
    <UserMenu />
  </div>
</header>
```

## Rules

- The home page (`src/app/page.tsx`) does NOT get a back link — it IS the home.
- All other pages must use `<UserMenu />` for the user icon (never a standalone Sign Out button).
- External profile links should open in a new tab (`target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`).
